  "combined_text": "--- Main Page ---\nTBB 122\nBack\nWeekday Breakfast\nWeekday Lunch\nWeekend Brunch\nAfternoon 3-5pm\nDinner\nDrinks\nScroll\nhours\nMONDAY\nclosed, see you soon!\nTuesday\ncoffee & pastry\n8am-5pm\nbreakfast:\n8am-11am\nlunch:\n11am-3pm\nafternoon\nbites\n:  3-4pm\ndinner:\nclosed\nwednesday-friday\ncoffee & pastry\n8am-5pm\nbreakfast:\n8am-11am\nlunch:\n11am-3pm\nafternoon\nbites\n:  3-5pm\ndinner:\n5-9pm (10pm on Friday)\nSaturday\ncoffee & pastry\n8am-5pm\nbrunch\n:  8am-3pm\nafternoon bites\n: 3-5pm\ndinner\n: 5-10pm\nSUNDAY\ncoffee & pastry\n8am-4pm\nbrunch\n:  8am-3pm\nDinner:\nClosed\nplease call to make a reservation for parties larger than 6 people\nparking is available in our lot and along roswell street. additional weekday parking is available at the alpharetta community center.\nevening and weekend only parking is available at 131 roswell street (white brick buildings)\nBook your TBB 122 reservation on Resy\nLOCATION\n122 Marietta Street\nAlpharetta, GA 30009\nCONTACT\n678-691-8364\ninfo@tbb122.com\n– tbb 122 –\n[ californian-inspired cuisine  ]\nTBB 122 is…\na community-focused full-service cafe and restaurant serving Alpharetta artisan goods and delicious, healthful meals prepared using local ingredients.Inspired by Californian design and cuisine, TBB is everything you love about Michele Sedgwick’s market favorite, Theo's Brother’s Bakery… and more. Along with full-service dine-in options, TBB 122 will offer prepared meals to-go as well as an extensive selection of hand-crafted pastries, breads, dips, and other goods, and a beautiful selection of seasonal retail items. Guests will be immediately feel welcomed in the warm, cozy atmosphere, fitted with banquet seating and nooks, wood accents, and spacious outdoor seating underneath a 150 year old oak tree surrounded by organically grown herbs and veggies and lush European landscaping.\nto Eat + drink\nbreakfast & lunch\ntues-fri 8-11am\ntues-fri 11am-3pm\ndinner\nwed, thurs, sun | 5-9pm\nfri-sat | 5-10pm\nweekend brunch\nsat-sun | 9am-3pm\ncoffee +pastries\ntues-sun | 8am-5pm\nlocal farms we partner with\nWatsonia Farms |  Monetta, SC\nJ. Calvert Farms | Bremen, AL\nBJ Reece Orchards |  Ellijay, GA\nMarsh Hen Mills | Edisto Island, SC\nMcEwen and Sons | Wilsonville, AL\nBeeler Family Farm | Le Mars, IA\nAdam Cox | Florence, AL\nga Honey Farm | cloudland canyon\nHaynes Farms | Culman, AL\nCornucopia Farms | Avera, GA\nEllijay Mushrooms | Ellijay, GA\nRolling Branch Farms | Naylor, GA\nSweet Grass Dairy | Thomasville, GA\natlanta dairies | Slocomb, AL\nRise N’ Shine organics | Calhoun, GA\nRock House creamery | Covington, GA\nBlits brothers mushroom company | Atlanta, Ga\nByne Blueberries | Waynesboro, GA\nupcoming events\n*NEW* wednesdays-saturdays | aperitivo hour\nJoin us every Wednesday-Saturday from 4-5:30pm for\n$7 spritzes, $6 select wines, and bites made for sharing – or enjoying all to yourself (we see you, frites + aioli).\nAperitivo Hour Menu\n2/25 | Barberas Tasting\nJoin us 2/25 at 5:30pm as we explore 5 Barbera wines!\n$45 + tax & gratuity per person\nreserve online,  pay  at time of event\nincludes tasting & seasonal hors d’oeuvres, plus pre-sale access to retail wines from tasting\nReserve\nHERE\n3/11 |  coming soon: wine tasting\n3/25 |  coming soon: wine tasting\n4/8  | coming soon: wine tasting\n4/22 | coming soon: wine tasting\n5/6 | coming soon: wine tasting\n5/20 | coming soon: wine tasting\n6/3 | coming soon: wine tasting\n6/17 |  coming soon: wine tasting\n7/1 |  coming soon: wine tasting\n7/15 |  coming soon: wine tasting\n7/21 |  coming soon: wine tasting\nInstagram\nFacebook\nkeep up with tbb:\nView fullsize\nView fullsize\nView fullsize\nView fullsize\n\n--- Page: /s/tbb-122-brunch-weekend-menu-20251212-print-ypyx.pdf ---\n%PDF-1.4\r%����\n628 0 obj\r<\n>\rendobj\r              \rxref\n628 28\n0000000016 00000 n\n0000001293 00000 n\n0000001452 00000 n\n0000011009 00000 n\n0000011509 00000 n\n0000012217 00000 n\n00000127